---
import SectionHead from "./SectionHead.astro";
---

<section
  id="about"
  class="px-6 sm:px-12 lg:px-20 pt-28 sm:pt-36 pb-24 bg-paper-deep border-y border-border"
>
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto">
    <SectionHead
      fig="07"
      name="the draftsman"
      title="Hey, <em>I'm Russ.</em>"
    />

    <div class="grid items-start gap-10 lg:grid-cols-[24rem_1fr]">
      <figure class="rise relative max-w-sm">
        <div class="card-plate overflow-hidden p-3">
          <img
            src="/images/russ-headshot2.webp"
            alt="Russ Gardner, the designer and builder behind generuss design"
            width="640"
            height="800"
            loading="lazy"
            class="photo-plate block aspect-[4/5] w-full object-cover"
          />
        </div>
        <figcaption class="mono-note mt-3">
          fig. 07a &middot; the human accountable
        </figcaption>
      </figure>

      <div class="max-w-xl lg:pt-4">
        <p class="rise text-lg sm:text-xl text-text" style="--rise-i: 1">
          <strong class="font-semibold"
            >20 years in sales taught me how people decide.</strong
          ><br />
          I bring that instinct to every pixel: no template, no guesswork, no junior
          handoffs. When you hire generuss design you get one person, start to finish,
          who has closed deals for two decades and now builds the pages that close
          them for you.
        </p>
        <p class="rise mt-5 text-base text-text-muted" style="--rise-i: 2">
          The AI tooling I build with gets a lot of attention. The part that
          matters: it lets one craftsman ship agency-grade work in 21 days,
          while the sales brain decides what deserves to be on the page at all.
        </p>

        <dl
          class="rise mt-10 grid grid-cols-3 gap-6 border-t border-border pt-7"
          style="--rise-i: 3"
        >
          <div>
            <dt class="mono-note order-2">yrs in sales</dt>
            <dd class="font-display text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-medium text-text">
              20+
            </dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt class="mono-note order-2">avg speed score</dt>
            <dd class="font-display text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-medium text-text">
              96
            </dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt class="mono-note order-2">star rated</dt>
            <dd class="font-display text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-medium text-text">
              5.0
            </dd>
          </div>
        </dl>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  dl div {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }
  dd {
    order: 1;
  }
  dt {
    order: 2;
    margin-top: 0.4rem;
  }
</style>
